Sentencas: Two techniques of spray pyrolysis, namely, electrostatic and pneumatic spray deposition, were used to deposit samaria-doped ceria (SDC) electrolyte and lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite (LSCF) cathode on cermet or metal supported anodes for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) operated at reduced temperature.
Titulo: Thin Film Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Deposited by Spray Pyrolysis

Sentencas: The deposition processes, the properties of the deposited films, and the electrochemical performances of the fabricated cells are reported in this paper.
Titulo: Thin Film Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Deposited by Spray Pyrolysis

Sentencas: The deposited SDC electrolytes were dense and gas-tight, and had good adhesion to the underlying anodes.
Titulo: Thin Film Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Deposited by Spray Pyrolysis

Sentencas: The deposited LSCF cathode had a preferred morphology to facilitate the transport of oxygen gas and effective contact with the electrolyte.
Titulo: Thin Film Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Deposited by Spray Pyrolysis

Sentencas: Button cell testing indicated that the SOFCs with electrolyte or cathode deposited by spray pyrolysis had good electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Thin Film Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Deposited by Spray Pyrolysis

Sentencas: This study demonstrated that spray pyrolysis is a cost-effective process for fabricating thin film SOFCs, especially metal supported SOFCs.
Titulo: Thin Film Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Deposited by Spray Pyrolysis
